title: Woman abducted at Sydney shopping centre - 9news.com.au
text:
Woman abducted at Sydney shopping centre By AAP 
Police hold serious concerns for a woman who was possibly abducted in Sydney's east. 
Officers were called to a shopping centre in Bondi Junction about 3pm on Tuesday after reports a woman was assaulted by a man, who then forced her into a van and left. 
The 35-year-old woman, Elizabeth Bell, is believed to be in the company of a 42-year-old man, William Curteis, and may be travelling in a white Toyota Hiace van with NSW registration RYD227. 
Police are urging anyone with information about Ms Bell to contact them immediately. Â© AAP 2017
